Vice President Mike Pence spoke with Prime Minister Nechirvan Barzani of Iraq's Kurdistan Regional Government. They discussed the security situation in Iraq's disputed territories and the need for continued U.S. support to stabilize these areas and allow for the return of displaced Iraqis. Vice President Pence commended Prime Minister Barzani for providing refuge for displaced civilians and leading efforts to protect religious components affected by ISIS. They also discussed opportunities to deepen the U.S. partnership with Kurdistan and counteract actors that seek to destabilize Iraq.